repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
Fixing https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/3164 by adding python threading logic to lock and release GIL. Plus some refactoring.
Specifically - the cause of the segment fault is that when the model are getting inferred by the runtime, the thread running "compute" function didn't acquired GIL which brought invalid access to the heap. Therefore added two functions - "PyOpLibProxy::GetGil()" and "PyOpLibProxy::PutGil()" to lock GIL and release when done. 
For the refactoring - just removed pywrapper which brought about too much inconvenience to consume  PyOP.
